The paper discusses the process of Test Case Generation (TCG) for software development, which falls under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper specifically focuses on Constraint Logic Programming (CLP) as a promising application field for TCG, which falls under the category of Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper also deals with object-oriented (OO) imperative languages, which falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of symbolic execution in TCG, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Overall, the paper covers topics that are relevant to multiple sub-categories in arXiv CS, but the most likely categories are cs.SE and cs.PL.
